  tunnelPool:
    state: 3
    arthurPool:
      sourceLines:
      - text: Sent into the curved tunnel.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: A blind entry into the pipe!
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: The handler executes a brilliant front cross while the dog is out of
          sight.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: Lost some traction exiting the tunnel on the turf.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: Sucked right into the wrong tunnel! An elimination!
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: Explodes out of the chute with tremendous speed.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: Excellent verbal command to pull the dog into the near entrance.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: "A slight delay inside the tunnel\u2014perhaps a momentary loss of
          footing."
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: Pops out and immediately acquires the next target.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: The handler needs to hustle to beat the dog to the exit.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: The tunnel is fully enclosed. The dog runs on pure instinct and training.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: A curved tunnel entry. The dog must commit without seeing the exit.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: The handler positions for a front cross while the dog navigates blind.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: Speed through the tunnel is critical. Every tenth counts.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: The dog's exit angle will determine the next obstacle approach.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: A tunnel-to-tunnel sequence. The dog must differentiate between entries.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: The fabric rustles as the dog blasts through. Pure speed.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: The handler's verbal cue at the entrance was perfectly timed.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: A slight hesitation at the exit. The dog reorients to the handler.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: Tunnel speed is a sign of confidence. This dog has it in spades.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: The dog's body low to the ground inside the tunnel. Optimal form.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: A smooth transition from tunnel to the next obstacle.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: The handler's position at the exit draws the dog forward.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: Tunnels are about trust. The dog trusts the handler's guidance.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: The dog accelerates through the tunnel without hesitation.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: A brilliant blind cross executed while the dog was out of sight.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: The tunnel entry was tight, but the dog committed fully.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: Exit speed is impressive. The dog explodes out of the chute.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: The handler barely beats the dog to the exit. Perfect timing.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: Tunnel navigation is second nature to this experienced dog.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: The curved tunnel tests the dog's ability to maintain momentum.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: A clean exit sets up the next obstacle perfectly.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: The dog's commitment to the tunnel entry was decisive.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: Tunnels add variety and challenge to any agility course.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: The dog's exit was perfectly aligned with the handler's position.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: A textbook tunnel run. No wasted motion, maximum speed.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: The handler's body language guided the dog through without verbal cues.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: Tunnel performance like this separates good teams from great ones.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: The dog's confidence in tunnels is evident. Full speed ahead.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: A flawless tunnel execution. Championship caliber.
        announcerType: 0
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
