    buckPool:
      sourceLines:
      - text: I once saw a guy eat a tire like that. Course, it was made of black
          licorice.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: Why don't they just fly over it? Oh, right. Dogs. I forgot.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: Look at the legs on that one. Think he could play shortstop for the
          Mets?
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: He knocked it down! Can we get a carpenter out here? This place is
          falling apart.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: I've jumped out of windows higher than that, Arthur. Mostly for romantic
          reasons.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: "I tried to jump over a fence once. Got stuck at the top. Like a pi\xF1ata."
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: Arthur, that dog has serious ups. Better than my vertical in high school.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: If I could jump like that, I'd never wait in line again. Just hop right
          over!
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: That dog's jumping is better than my jump shots. And I played basketball.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: I wonder if the dog thinks the bars are snakes. 'Don't touch the danger
          sticks!'
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: I tried to do a broad jump at the beach once. Pulled a hamstring. Worth
          it.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: That dog has the spring-loaded legs of a cartoon character.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: If I jumped like that, my knees would file a workers' comp claim.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: Arthur, I think the dog is part kangaroo. Look at those hops!
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: I once tried to jump a tire. Got my foot stuck. Fire department had
          to come.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: That dog makes jumping look easy. Meanwhile, I struggle with stairs.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: I should get a trampoline. Learn to jump like that. My doctor would
          be thrilled.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: That dog is flying! Can we get him a pilot's license?
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: I tried to do a flying leap once. Landed in a fountain. 10/10 would
          do again.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: That dog's vertical leap could win a slam dunk contest.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: I wonder if the dog practices jumping at home. Like, over the couch.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: If that dog played volleyball, he'd never let a ball hit the ground.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: I think the dog is part gazelle. Look at that grace!
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: I need those jumping lessons. My long jump days are over, but maybe
          vertical?
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: Arthur, that dog has been hitting the gym. Look at those quads!
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: I tried to jump over a puddle once. Ended up in the puddle. Classic
          Buck.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: That dog jumps like he's on a pogo stick. Boing, boing, boing!
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: If the Olympics had a dog jumping event, this dog would get gold.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: I think the dog is auditioning for a superhero movie. Captain Canine!
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: That dog has better jumping form than my karate kid impression.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
