    buckPool:
      sourceLines:
      - text: He's sniffing the ground! I think he found oil, Arthur. We're rich!
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: The dog is looking at me. Stop looking at me! I don't have the jerky
          anymore!
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: Arthur, what if the dog just speaks Spanish and doesn't understand
          the lady?
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: He's making his own course. I respect that. A true artist doesn't follow
          lines.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: Is there a penalty if the dog just goes over to the crowd and asks
          for a hot dog?
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: Well, that was a trainwreck. Should we go down there and help? I have
          a whistle.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: The dog is looking at the handler like she owes him money.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: I've seen better focus from a squirrel with ADHD.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: That dog just noped right out of that obstacle. I respect the honesty.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: If this were a test, that dog just failed with flying colors.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: I think the dog is having an existential crisis. 'Why am I running?'
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: That's me every Monday morning. Just completely lost and confused.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: I once forgot where I parked. This dog forgot where he's running. Similar
          energy.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: If dogs had Yelp reviews, that run would get one star. Would not recommend.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: Arthur, I think the dog is staging a protest. 'No more obstacles!'
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: I've seen better direction from a tourist without a map.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: That dog is definitely freelance running. No rules, no boundaries.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: If confusion were a sport, that dog would be the champion.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: I think the dog just did an obstacle course of his own design. Interesting
          choices.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: That's the dog version of 'I'm not mad, I'm just disappointed.'
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: I tried to follow that run and now I need a therapist.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: 'If the dog wrote a memoir, it would be titled ''Lost and Confused:
          My Journey.'''
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: I think the dog just realized he's not a cat. Explains a lot.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: That's me trying to assemble IKEA furniture. Just random parts going
          everywhere.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: If chaos were an art form, that dog would be Picasso.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: I think the dog just invented a new sport. Chaotic Running. Patent
          pending.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: Arthur, I think the dog is having a mid-life crisis. 'What am I doing
          with my life?'
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: That run was so bad, even the cat judging from the sidelines looked
          embarrassed.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: If that dog were a GPS, it would say 'Recalculating' every two seconds.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
      - text: I think the dog just realized the treat isn't at the finish line. Motivation
          lost.
        announcerType: 1
        voiceIdOverride: 
        tags: []
        priority: 50
